N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 40.33 - Information services

State Regulations

The commissioner, with the advice and assistance of the
advisory board, is hereby authorized to contract with any person or persons to
provide for informational services designed to keep producers and others
informed on milk marketing and dairy product research, promotion, advertising, education and publicity programs and any other dairy industry information
deemed important, and to expend such monies as may be available and required
pursuant to this Part to obtain and disseminate such
information. Notes
